{
  "analysis": "Still 720x400 grayscale with only 2 colors - looks like a very dark or nearly blank screen. The VM may still be booting, or it may be at a DOS prompt waiting for input. Let me check the pixel content and see if we need to wait longer or if it needs keyboard input to start Windows.",
  "plan": "Check if the screen has any content by examining the image more closely. Also try waiting longer - Windows 3.11 may need to auto-start or we might need to look at the boot process more carefully.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 -c \"\nwith open('/tmp/vm-screen2.ppm', 'rb') as f:\n    data = f.read()\n# Count non-zero bytes\nprint(f'Total size: {len(data)}')\nprint(f'Header (first 100 bytes): {data[:100]}')\n# Check if mostly zeros or mostly 255\npixels = data.split(b'\\n', 2)[2]  # skip header lines\nzeros = pixels.count(b'\\x00')\nffs = pixels.count(b'\\xff')\nprint(f'Black pixels: {zeros}, White pixels: {ffs}')\nprint(f'Other: {len(pixels) - zeros - ffs}')\n\"\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sleep 15 && echo 'screendump /tmp/vm-screen3.ppm' | socat - UNIX-CONNECT:/tmp/qemu-monitor.sock\n",
      "duration": 20.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "convert /tmp/vm-screen3.ppm -colorspace sRGB /tmp/vm-screen3.png 2>&1 && identify /tmp/vm-screen3.png\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}
